have killed the cast from Stab 1?

918
01:06:26,800 --> 01:06:29,080
Huh? Or Stab 2? Why me?
What--John, what did we do wrong?

919
01:06:29,320 --> 01:06:31,520
Hollywood is full of criminals
whose careers are flourishing.

920
01:06:31,760 --> 01:06:33,880
I'm not a criminal!
I was questioned.

921
01:06:34,120 --> 01:06:35,880
Yeah, but that's all.
I was questioned. That's it.

922
01:06:36,120 --> 01:06:38,840
- That's good foryour mystique.
- You think it will help me get work?

923
01:06:39,080 --> 01:06:40,960
Roman. John.

924
01:06:41,200 --> 01:06:44,000
Jennifer, and guests.
To what do I owe the honour?

925
01:06:44,240 --> 01:06:47,880
- Rina Reynolds.
- Rina Reynolds? Who's Rina Reynolds?

926
01:06:48,120 --> 01:06:51,440
Why don't you head to the house?
Tell everybody not to cut
the cake without me.

927
01:06:51,680 --> 01:06:53,880
- Oh, God, I forgot. Your birthday.
- Yeah.

928
01:06:54,120 --> 01:06:56,760
- Happy birthday, Roman.
- Yeah, as if life isn't tragic enough.

929
01:06:57,000 --> 01:07:01,520
Shut the doors behind you, please.

930
01:07:02,400 --> 01:07:04,600
So, you knew
Sidney Prescott's mother.

931
01:07:04,840 --> 01:07:07,920
- Who?
- Rina Reynolds?

932
01:07:08,160 --> 01:07:11,200
Do you know how many actors have
worked for me? Hundreds. Thousands.

933
01:07:11,440 --> 01:07:14,600
- He didn't say she was an actor.
- Good catch.

934
01:07:14,840 --> 01:07:17,000
- So what's the point?
- Uh, no point.

935
01:07:17,240 --> 01:07:19,920
I'm just gonna give, uh,
Detective Kincaid a call.

936
01:07:20,160 --> 01:07:23,760
I remember. She was a bit player
in a couple of my movies.

937
01:07:24,000 --> 01:07:26,320
- A nobody. So what does it matter?
- Oh, come on.

938
01:07:26,560 --> 01:07:29,960
You have made millions
off the story of her murder.

939
01:07:30,200 --> 01:07:32,920
You're obsessed with her,
and you're obsessed with her daughter!

940
01:07:33,160 --> 01:07:36,160
All right, easy, Geraldo.
Why don't you tell us the truth?

941
01:07:36,400 --> 01:07:40,240
What the hell are you guys getting at?
I make horror films, that's what I do.

942
01:07:40,480 --> 01:07:42,400
The studio came to me with Stab.

943
01:07:42,640 --> 01:07:45,240
They came to me.
Check it out.

944
01:07:45,480 --> 01:07:48,000
- But you knew who she was.
- When we did the first Stab...

945
01:07:48,240 --> 01:07:50,360
I realized I had known
Maureen Prescott before.

946
01:07:50,600 --> 01:07:52,800
I mean, as Rina.

947
01:07:53,040 --> 01:07:56,640
I couldn't tell anyone.
Can you imagine the press?

948
01:07:56,880 --> 01:07:59,120
And now?
I mean, murders on your set.

949
01:07:59,360 --> 01:08:01,600
- And-And still you say nothing?
- Get real.

950
01:08:01,840 --> 01:08:04,120
- That would make me a suspect.
-Just because you knew her?

951
01:08:04,360 --> 01:08:06,560
- Yeah.
- I don't think so.

952
01:08:06,800 --> 01:08:10,400
Just what did happen to Maureen
when she was in Hollywood?

953
01:08:11,120 --> 01:08:13,600
Now, you listen to me, Lois Lane.
Let it go. It's dead and buried.

954
01:08:13,840 --> 01:08:16,920
How would you like to see it
dug up on national TV?

955
01:08:17,160 --> 01:08:20,520
Why don't you tell me
what happened?

956
01:08:21,680 --> 01:08:24,760
It was in the '70s.
Everything was different.

957
01:08:25,000 --> 01:08:28,560
I was well-known for my parties.
Rina knew what they were.

958
01:08:28,800 --> 01:08:32,960
It was for girls like her to meet men.
Men who could get them parts...

959
01:08:33,200 --> 01:08:34,960
if they made
the right impression.

960
01:08:35,200 --> 01:08:37,280
Nothing happened to her
that she didn't invite...

961
01:08:37,520 --> 01:08:40,600
in one way or another
no matter what she said afterwards.

962
01:08:40,840 --> 01:08:43,880
- Are you saying she--
- I'm saying things got out of hand.

963
01:08:44,120 --> 01:08:47,840
Maybe they did take advantage of her.
You know, Maybe the sad truth is...

964
01:08:48,080 --> 01:08:51,480
this is not the city
for innocents.

965
01:08:51,720 --> 01:08:54,520
No charges were brought.
And the bottom line is...

966
01:08:54,760 --> 01:08:57,200
Rina Reynolds
wouldn't play by the rules.

967
01:08:57,440 --> 01:08:59,520
You wanna get ahead in Hollywood?

968
01:08:59,760 --> 01:09:04,440
You gotta play the game, or go home.

969
01:09:08,840 --> 01:09:11,280
What do you know
about trilogies?

970
01:09:11,520 --> 01:09:14,760
- You mean, like movie trilogies?
- You seem to like movies, Detective.

971
01:09:15,000 --> 01:09:19,160
Call me Mark, would you? 'Cause
I'm gonna keep calling you Sidney.

972
01:09:19,400 --> 01:09:23,080
I'll call you Mark when
you catch the killer, Detective.

973
01:09:23,800 --> 01:09:27,680
All I know about movie trilogies
is that in the third one...

974
01:09:27,920 --> 01:09:31,600
all bets are off.

975
01:09:31,640 --> 01:09:33,560
- Did you request this case?
- No. They tend to put me...

976
01:09:33,800 --> 01:09:35,560
on the ones that deal
with the business.

977
01:09:35,800 --> 01:09:38,760
I grew up here,
and I know my way around the studios.

978
01:09:39,000 --> 01:09:41,120
Huh.

979
01:09:41,360 --> 01:09:44,600
Must be exciting.
Beautiful place, beautiful people.

980
01:09:44,840 --> 01:09:48,440
To me, Hollywood is about death.

981
01:09:48,920 --> 01:09:51,360
Excuse me?

982
01:09:51,600 --> 01:09:54,800
I'm a homicide detective, remember?

983
01:09:55,040 --> 01:09:57,640
And when you see what I see
day in and day out...

984
01:09:57,880 --> 01:10:00,200
the violence
that people do to each other...

985
01:10:00,440 --> 01:10:02,200
you get haunted.

986
01:10:02,440 --> 01:10:05,800
I think you know about that.

987
01:10:06,520 --> 01:10:08,640
What do you mean?

988
01:10:08,880 --> 01:10:11,760
I know what it's like
to see ghosts that don't go away.

989
01:10:12,000 --> 01:10:17,080
To be watching a scary movie in
your head, whether you want to or not.

990
01:10:17,360 --> 01:10:21,960
Watching it alone.

991
01:10:22,800 --> 01:10:25,200
Ghosts are tough.
You can't shoot ghosts.

992
01:10:25,440 --> 01:10:28,120
Can't arrest ghosts.

993
01:10:28,360 --> 01:10:31,640
But the best way to stop being
haunted is to be with people.

994
01:10:31,880 --> 01:10:33,720
You're here, you're not hiding.

995
01:10:33,960 --> 01:10:38,720
You've done the right thing,
Miss Prescott.

996
01:10:41,600 --> 01:10:45,280
What did you know about your mother?

997
01:10:48,280 --> 01:10:50,720
I always thought
I had the perfect mom.

998
01:10:50,960 --> 01:10:54,320
Perfect family.

999
01:10:55,240 --> 01:11:00,080
Till I found out I was wrong.
She, um--

1000
01:11:01,320 --> 01:11:06,080
She had a secret life, and I tried
to understand that, and, um...

1001
01:11:06,320 --> 01:11:11,760
soon as I thought that I had,
more secrets.

1002
01:11:13,840 --> 01:11:16,640
I don't know who my mom was.

1003
01:11:16,880 --> 01:11:20,560
You know who she was to you.

1004
01:11:23,480 --> 01:11:25,360
Here's the deal.
I'm off to search the set.

1005
01:11:25,600 --> 01:11:29,560
I think what you saw is real.
That's the good news.

1006
01:11:29,800 --> 01:11:31,800
- How is that good news?
- Because that means...

1007
01:11:32,040 --> 01:11:34,880
that we're dealing with
an ordinary flesh-and-blood killer.

1008
01:11:35,120 --> 01:11:38,400
- And I know how
to handle guys like that.
- Oh, yeah? How?

1009
01:11:38,640 --> 01:11:42,920
Catch him or kill him.

1010
01:11:44,880 --> 01:11:48,640
Hey, Detective.

1011
01:11:48,880 --> 01:11:52,720
What's your favourite
scary movie?

1012
01:11:54,920 --> 01:11:58,280
My life.

1013
01:11:59,720 --> 01:12:02,160
Mine too.

1014
01:12:02,880 --> 01:12:04,680
We have to think.
Strategize.

1015
01:12:04,920 --> 01:12:07,560
- Milton's the key to everything.
- He's a pervert, he's not a killer.

1016
01:12:07,800 --> 01:12:10,400
He's gotta be involved somehow.
We should follow him.

1017
01:12:10,640 --> 01:12:12,400
We're gonna go back to the precinct and
we're gonna tell Kincaid and Sidney...

1018
01:12:12,640 --> 01:12:14,600
what we found out.

1019
01:12:14,840 --> 01:12:18,040
My Gale would be much more aggressive.
My Gale would suspect everybody.

1020
01:12:18,280 --> 01:12:21,880
- My Gale would--
- Shut up!
- Shut up!

1021
01:12:23,440 --> 01:12:25,880
- Riley here.
- Dewey, it's Sidney.
- Hey, Sid.

1022
01:12:26,120 --> 01:12:27,960
- I'm with Gale.
We're on our way to see you.
- No.

1023
01:12:28,200 --> 01:12:31,400
Listen, I'm not at the station.
John Milton called me and said
he had something to tell me.

1024
01:12:31,640 --> 01:12:33,840
Something about my mom.
I'm going to meet him at his house.

1025
01:12:34,080 --> 01:12:36,160
Wait, Sid, I'm not so sure
that's a good idea.

1026
01:12:36,400 --> 01:12:39,120
It's okay. Kincaid's with me.
I've got official big-time...

1027
01:12:39,360 --> 01:12:42,480
L.A.P.D. protection, but
I'd feel better if you were there.

1028
01:12:42,720 --> 01:12:46,640
- We're on our way, but still, Sid--
- Thanks.

1029
01:12:46,880 --> 01:12:51,960
- What?
- Looks like we're going
to that party after all.

1030
01:13:01,000 --> 01:13:03,600
Hey, guys. Come on in.
Join the party.

1031
01:13:03,840 --> 01:13:05,640
Yeah, well, actually,
we're here to see Sidney.

1032
01:13:05,880 --> 01:13:07,840
- Really? Sidney's here.
- Where?

1033
01:13:08,080 --> 01:13:11,120
- Where's Sidney?
- She's right there!

1034
01:13:11,360 --> 01:13:14,520
Jesus!
Not "Sidney," Sidney.

1035
01:13:14,760 --> 01:13:18,000
- Like I'm "Gale" and she's Gale.
- Sidney Prescott?

1036
01:13:18,240 --> 01:13:20,840
- Yeah.
- No, I'd never invite her here.

1037
01:13:21,080 --> 01:13:24,520
- She's on her way.
- Well, the more the merrier.

1038
01:13:24,760 --> 01:13:28,320
God, this house is incredible.

1039
01:13:28,560 --> 01:13:31,320
-It's old Hollywood.
-Yeah. Could the dude have more money?

1040
01:13:31,560 --> 01:13:34,320
Supposedly, Milton has
a secret screening room...

1041
01:13:34,560 --> 01:13:36,320
that was like the scene
back in the '70s, you know.

1042
01:13:36,560 --> 01:13:40,520
It was, like, drinks and drugs
and girls and movies and shit.

1043
01:13:40,760 --> 01:13:43,320
Wow! Wish I could've seen it.

1044
01:13:43,560 --> 01:13:45,360
Big old screening room
shouldn't be too hard to find.

1045
01:13:45,600 --> 01:13:47,360
I'm gonna go--
I'm gonna go check this place out.

1046
01:13:47,600 --> 01:13:50,840
Whoa, whoa, whoa!
Just one damn minute.
There's a psycho killer on the loose.

1047
01:13:51,080 --> 01:13:53,440
And you want to go traipsing around
this gigantic mansion?

1048
01:13:53,680 --> 01:13:55,920
Have you ever actually seen
the Stab movies? Every time...

1049
01:13:56,160 --> 01:13:58,600
this dude enters a room,
he ends up a goddam shish kebab.

1050
01:13:58,840 --> 01:14:01,720
- I'll go with you, Roman.
- There you go. You guys wanna come?

1051
01:14:01,960 --> 01:14:05,720
It'll be okay.
We're gonna stick together.

1052
01:14:05,960 --> 01:14:09,320
-You're not stickin'. Wait up.
-We're gonna stay here and wait for Sid.

1053
01:14:09,560 --> 01:14:12,560
We'll be right back!

1054
01:14:12,800 --> 01:14:15,720
If-If you were a screening room...

1055
01:14:15,960 --> 01:14:19,320
where would you be?

1056
01:14:20,560 --> 01:14:23,920
I bet in the basement.

1057
01:14:25,080 --> 01:14:28,920
I don't like basements.

1058
01:14:31,240 --> 01:14:34,600
Ooh, it's spooky.

1059
01:14:45,280 --> 01:14:47,160
- Ooh, Weredad.
- Damn, it's dark in here.

1060
01:14:47,400 --> 01:14:49,840
- I loved that movie.
- Forget the movie!
What if Milton's crazy...

1061
01:14:50,080 --> 01:14:52,480
and he's gonna jump outta his screening
room with a sling blade or something?

1062
01:14:52,720 --> 01:14:56,080
- He won't.
- You sure about that?

1063
01:15:00,240 --> 01:15:03,560
- What's down there?
- Zombies and aliens.

1064
01:15:03,800 --> 01:15:06,120
You know, what you look like
without make-up, Jennifer.

1065
01:15:06,360 --> 01:15:09,360
Jesus. Stop pretending
I wasn't the best you've ever had.

1066
01:15:09,600 --> 01:15:14,960
- Oh, stop pretending I even remember.
- Stop pretending!

1067
01:15:18,480 --> 01:15:21,760
Roman?

1068
01:15:31,800 --> 01:15:35,160
Roman?

1069
01:15:38,440 --> 01:15:41,600
- Any sign of her?
- No.

1070
01:15:41,840 --> 01:15:44,000
This is so strange.

1071
01:15:44,240 --> 01:15:46,000
It sure is.

1072
01:15:46,240 --> 01:15:48,160
Dewey, do you have caller I.D.
on your cell phone?

1073
01:15:48,400 --> 01:15:51,920
-Yeah.
-All right, use it and-and press "send."

1074
01:16:00,400 --> 01:16:03,760
What the hell?

1075
01:16:13,400 --> 01:16:17,240
What is this thing?

1076
01:16:17,840 --> 01:16:21,840
Is this what he--
What the hell?

1077
01:16:23,360 --> 01:16:25,560
Dewey, he's got our voices.

1078
01:16:25,800 --> 01:16:27,560
He's got Sid.

1079
01:16:27,800 --> 01:16:29,560
He's got us all.

1080
01:16:29,800 --> 01:16:33,360
- Oh, my God. We gotta find her.
- Come on.

1081
01:16:33,600 --> 01:16:35,880
All right, take the gun.

1082
01:16:36,120 --> 01:16:38,240
Go find Roman and Jennifer.
I'm gonna get the others.

1083
01:16:38,480 --> 01:16:41,840
- Be careful.
- You too.

1084
01:16:42,960 --> 01:16:48,480
Tyson! Angelina!
You up there?

1085
01:16:49,320 --> 01:16:52,000
- Roman!
- Tyson!

1086
01:16:52,240 --> 01:16:54,360
Angelina!

1087
01:16:54,600 --> 01:16:57,360
Damn it!

1088
01:16:57,600 --> 01:16:59,440
Okay, come on.
We gotta get out of here.

1089
01:16:59,680 --> 01:17:01,680
- Where's Angelina?
- I don't know. She went in here.

1090
01:17:01,920 --> 01:17:03,880
- I came in after her. Now she's gone.
- Great.

1091
01:17:04,120 --> 01:17:08,720
- What's wrong?
- Looks like Stab 3
is back in production.

1092
01:17:10,280 --> 01:17:13,440
Roman!

1093
01:17:13,680 --> 01:17:17,600
Jennifer!

1094
01:17:27,280 --> 01:17:31,120
Jennifer!

1095
01:17:34,720 --> 01:17:37,600
Roman!

1096
01:17:37,840 --> 01:17:41,200
Jennifer!

1097
01:17:47,920 --> 01:17:52,200
Roman?

1098
01:18:06,480 --> 01:18:08,240
- Is he dead?
- Yeah, very.

1099
01:18:08,480 --> 01:18:12,400
Dewey! Dewey!

1100
01:18:15,760 --> 01:18:18,520
Dewey?

1101
01:18:18,760 --> 01:18:21,120
Dewey!

1102
01:18:21,360 --> 01:18:23,480
God, I'm sorry.
Jennifer, Gale, look.

1103
01:18:23,720 --> 01:18:26,080
- I found a secret passage.
- Roman's dead.

1104
01:18:26,320 --> 01:18:28,680
- What?
- The killer's here.
- What?
- Come on.

1105
01:18:28,920 --> 01:18:32,240
- Let go of me! I'm getting out of here!
- You're not safe alone!

1106
01:18:32,480 --> 01:18:34,240
Listen to me!

1107
01:18:34,480 --> 01:18:38,400
I did not fuck that pig Milton
to get a leading role...

1108
01:18:38,640 --> 01:18:43,880
just to die here with second-rate
celebrities like you two!

1109
01:18:45,760 --> 01:18:48,800
- Gale! I'm up here.
- Come on.

1110
01:18:49,040 --> 01:18:52,320
- Dewey!
- You guys should get out too.

1111
01:18:52,560 --> 01:18:56,400
It's crazy to still be here.

1112
01:19:01,400 --> 01:19:05,760
- Wait!
- Come on!

1113
01:19:19,680 --> 01:19:22,480
- Dewey!
- Gale, Jennifer, up here!

1114
01:19:22,720 --> 01:19:25,320
Dewey, here.
He got Roman and Angelina too.

1115
01:19:25,560 --> 01:19:29,240
- We'll be safer if we
stick together, won't we?
- Of course. Why--

1116
01:19:31,280 --> 01:19:33,000
What's goin' on?
Oh, shit!

1117
01:19:33,240 --> 01:19:36,440
- Hey!
- Dewey!

1118
01:19:36,480 --> 01:19:39,280
Dewey!

1119
01:19:39,520 --> 01:19:42,800
No!

1120
01:19:51,160 --> 01:19:54,240
Help! Police!
Help! Help!

1121
01:19:54,480 --> 01:19:58,520
Police! Help!

1122
01:20:04,840 --> 01:20:08,280
Oh, you motherfucker!

1123
01:20:43,760 --> 01:20:47,120
Damn!

1124
01:20:49,840 --> 01:20:54,520
Dewey! Dewey!

1125
01:20:56,680 --> 01:21:00,680
Behind the mirror, Dewey!

1126
01:21:01,400 --> 01:21:03,640
Gale! Get away! Dewey!

1127
01:21:03,880 --> 01:21:05,960
- Do you hear something?
- Get away from me, you asshole.

1128
01:21:06,200 --> 01:21:10,680
- Get away from me! You don't scare me!
- Look, Gale. The mirror's moving.

1129
01:21:10,920 --> 01:21:14,120
- Gale! Gale!
- Stand back, Gale.

1130
01:21:14,360 --> 01:21:17,360
You can't kill me. I'm the killer
in Stab 3. I'm the killer!

1131
01:21:17,600 --> 01:21:21,680
Gale, cover!

1132
01:21:22,240 --> 01:21:25,680
Dewey!

1133
01:21:34,560 --> 01:21:36,800
- Tyson!
- Tyson!

1134
01:21:37,040 --> 01:21:38,800
I'm gonna check down here.
You call for help.

1135
01:21:39,040 --> 01:21:41,160
Okay.

1136
01:21:41,400 --> 01:21:44,320
Tyson!

1137
01:21:44,560 --> 01:21:47,920
- Tyson?
- Any sign of him?

1138
01:21:48,160 --> 01:21:51,600
- No.
- All right. I'm gonna check out front.

1139
01:21:57,080 --> 01:22:00,440
Dew--

1140
01:22:23,240 --> 01:22:26,600
Gale!

1141
01:22:27,440 --> 01:22:31,200
Gale!

1142
01:22:31,800 --> 01:22:34,080
Gale!

1143
01:22:34,320 --> 01:22:38,160
- Dewey?
- Gale!

1144
01:22:39,480 --> 01:22:42,840
Gale!

1145
01:22:46,280 --> 01:22:48,680
- Who is this?
- Dewey, it's me.

1146
01:22:48,920 --> 01:22:51,680
Gale, where are you?

1147
01:22:51,920 --> 01:22:54,200
I'm in the basement.
I'm trapped.

1148
01:22:54,440 --> 01:22:58,040
- Where?
- There's a door in the kitchen.

1149
01:22:59,040 --> 01:23:02,480
Hurry.

1150
01:23:04,520 --> 01:23:08,320
Wait. How do I know this is
you, Gale, and not the killer?

1151
01:23:08,560 --> 01:23:11,800
Dewey, open the fucking door.
It's me.

1152
01:23:12,040 --> 01:23:14,600
Well, don't you think that's
what the killer would say?

1153
01:23:14,840 --> 01:23:21,000
Come on. He's out cold
at the bottom of the stairs.

1154
01:23:21,680 --> 01:23:25,200
Hey!

1155
01:23:36,160 --> 01:23:40,080
Dewey. Dewey.

1156
01:23:48,840 --> 01:23:50,640
All right, all right.
It's pizza, not a party.

1157
01:23:50,880 --> 01:23:55,120
Everybody get back to work.
Anybody seen my fuckin' partner?

1158
01:23:55,360 --> 01:23:58,720
Hey, Morgan,
what did you pay?

1159
01:24:44,640 --> 01:24:47,680
- Hello?
- Hello?

1160
01:24:47,920 --> 01:24:50,240
- Who is this?
- Who is this?

1161
01:24:50,480 --> 01:24:55,360
- Um, w-who's calling?
- Um, w-who's calling?

1162
01:24:55,600 --> 01:25:00,640
Gale, Dewey, whoever, um, call me back.
I can only hear myself.

1163
01:25:00,880 --> 01:25:05,240
I only hear you too, Sidney.

1164
01:25:05,400 --> 01:25:08,560
- Who is this?
- The question isn't who I am.

1165
01:25:08,800 --> 01:25:12,360
The question is:
Who's with me?

1166
01:25:12,600 --> 01:25:14,360
- Sidney, stay away!
- Sidney!

1167
01:25:14,600 --> 01:25:17,800
Don't do it. If you do one thing
to attract attention to yourself...

1168
01:25:18,040 --> 01:25:20,600
one thing,
I'll kill them both.

1169
01:25:20,840 --> 01:25:26,080
Now, do you have somewhere
we can be alone?

1170
01:25:26,320 --> 01:25:30,440
- Yes.
- Yeah. Go there.

1171
01:25:35,520 --> 01:25:38,080
Oh, it's hard being friends
with you, Sidney.

1172
01:25:38,320 --> 01:25:41,160
When you're friends with Sidney,
you die.

1173
01:25:41,400 --> 01:25:45,520
Well, these friends don't have to,
Sidney. It's up to you.

1174
01:25:45,760 --> 01:25:47,600
- How do I know their voices are--
- Are real?

1175
01:25:47,840 --> 01:25:49,680
How do you know
you're not hearing things?

1176
01:25:49,920 --> 01:25:54,840
How do you know I'm not someone
in your head? Somewhere you know.

1177
01:25:55,080 --> 01:25:57,360
- Don't come here, Sidney!
- Dewey!

1178
01:25:57,600 --> 01:26:00,560
- Or do you?
- You're dead.

1179
01:26:00,800 --> 01:26:02,960
I don't want them.
I want you.

1180
01:26:03,200 --> 01:26:05,680
It's simple.
You show yourself, they survive.

1181
01:26:05,920 --> 01:26:08,200
- You run, they die.
- Oh, God!

1182
01:26:08,440 --> 01:26:12,160
Don't you wanna know, Sidney,
who killed her?

1183
01:26:12,400 --> 01:26:15,600
Don't you wanna know
who killed your mother?

1184
01:26:15,840 --> 01:26:17,600
- Have you seen Kincaid?
- Yeah, I saw him go out.

1185
01:26:17,840 --> 01:26:19,440
- Wallace is still lookin' for him.
- Where?

1186
01:26:19,680 --> 01:26:23,480
She'd have been so happy, Sidney,
to know we'd be together.

1187
01:26:23,720 --> 01:26:28,800
- Where?
- I'll call you when you're on your way.

1188
01:26:31,160 --> 01:26:35,200
Shit. Shit. Shit.

1189
01:27:39,640 --> 01:27:43,560
Holy shit.

1190
01:27:51,440 --> 01:27:53,640
- What?
- You follow directions well, Sidney.

1191
01:27:53,880 --> 01:27:55,840
Now, welcome to the final act.

1192
01:27:56,080 --> 01:27:58,560
See that metal detector?

1193
01:27:58,800 --> 01:28:02,560
Use it.

1194
01:28:05,280 --> 01:28:09,640
All over, Sidney.
Everywhere.

1195
01:28:12,680 --> 01:28:17,760
Everywhere.
The other leg too.

1196
01:28:20,400 --> 01:28:23,920
Show it to me.

1197
01:28:27,840 --> 01:28:31,200
Throw it in the pool.

1198
01:28:32,840 --> 01:28:34,600
Now, come inside, Sidney.

1199
01:28:34,840 --> 01:28:37,520
No fucking way. How do I know
they're not dead already?

1200
01:28:37,760 --> 01:28:40,840
They're right inside,
waiting for you.

1201
01:28:41,080 --> 01:28:44,440
Look for yourself.

1202
01:28:54,120 --> 01:28:58,920
Now that we're all here,
the party can begin.

1203
01:28:59,160 --> 01:29:02,280
- Dewey.
- Sid.

1204
01:29:02,520 --> 01:29:05,280
- Where is he?
- I don't know.

1205
01:29:05,520 --> 01:29:09,280
He's right there!

1206
01:29:13,680 --> 01:29:16,200
Oh, shit.

1207
01:29:16,440 --> 01:29:18,040
Think again.

1208
01:29:18,280 --> 01:29:22,040
It's your turn to scream, asshole.

1209
01:29:23,840 --> 01:29:28,040
Yeah!

1210
01:29:31,000 --> 01:29:34,200
- It's okay.Just give me a second.
- Okay.

1211
01:29:34,440 --> 01:29:39,280
- Hurry, Sid.
- Sidney? Sidney?

1212
01:29:40,520 --> 01:29:44,280
Where is he?

1213
01:29:45,960 --> 01:29:49,400
Be careful!

1214
01:29:54,880 --> 01:29:58,160
I heard shots. Tyson's dead.
What's goin' on?

1215
01:29:58,400 --> 01:30:00,840
- What're you doin' here, Kincaid?
- Lookin' for you.

1216
01:30:01,080 --> 01:30:03,960
Tyson said there was a party here
tonight, and I thought, uh-oh.

1217
01:30:04,200 --> 01:30:06,040
Third act celebration.
Thought I better check it out.

1218
01:30:06,280 --> 01:30:10,040
Alone?
Where's your partner?

1219
01:30:12,320 --> 01:30:15,000
Hey, Miss Prescott.

1220
01:30:15,240 --> 01:30:19,760
I'm here to help.
Put the gun down.

1221
01:30:20,640 --> 01:30:23,920
Put the gun down.

1222
01:30:26,600 --> 01:30:30,520
No!

1223
01:30:33,880 --> 01:30:38,120
Sid! Wake up, Sid!
Sid, come on!

1224
01:30:38,360 --> 01:30:42,080
- Wake up!
- Sidney!

1225
01:30:42,320 --> 01:30:44,520
Sid, shoot him! Sid!

1226
01:30:44,760 --> 01:30:48,320
Shoot the fucker!

1227
01:30:48,560 --> 01:30:52,760
Shoot him!

1228
01:30:55,800 --> 01:30:58,640
You want me, motherfucker?
Come and get me.

1229
01:30:58,880 --> 01:31:02,960
Run!

1230
01:31:47,600 --> 01:31:50,440
Sid.

1231
01:31:50,680 --> 01:31:53,920
Sid.

1232
01:31:54,160 --> 01:31:59,520
Come in here, please.

1233
01:32:00,360 --> 01:32:04,160
It's just me, Sid.

1234
01:32:04,400 --> 01:32:07,960
Oh, I was so pretty.

1235
01:32:08,200 --> 01:32:11,320
Everybody loved me.

1236
01:32:11,560 --> 01:32:15,840
Have you missed me, Sidney?

1237
01:32:16,400 --> 01:32:21,840
Would you like to hold me
one last time?

1238
01:32:22,160 --> 01:32:24,800
What's the matter?
What are you staring at?

1239
01:32:25,040 --> 01:32:30,800
Don't you remember your mother?

1240
01:32:40,280 --> 01:32:42,200
You're not going anywhere, Sidney.

1241
01:32:42,440 --> 01:32:48,040
It's time you came to terms
with me and with Mother.

1242
01:32:48,960 --> 01:32:51,600
Maybe you never
knew her at all, Sidney.

1243
01:32:51,840 --> 01:32:56,600
Maybe you just can't get past
the surface of things.

1244
01:32:56,840 --> 01:33:00,360
- Who the hell are you?
- The other half of you.

1245
01:33:00,600 --> 01:33:04,360
I searched for a mother too,
an actress named Rina Reynolds.

1246
01:33:04,600 --> 01:33:06,400
Tried to find her my whole life.

1247
01:33:06,640 --> 01:33:09,320
And four years ago,
I actually tracked her down.

1248
01:33:09,560 --> 01:33:12,560
Knocked at her door, thinking
she'd welcome me with open arms.

1249
01:33:12,800 --> 01:33:17,000
But she had a new life
and a new name: Maureen Prescott.

1250
01:33:17,240 --> 01:33:19,040
You were the only child
she claimed, Sidney.

1251
01:33:19,280 --> 01:33:22,000
She shut me out
in the cold forever.

1252
01:33:22,240 --> 01:33:26,160
Her own son.

1253
01:33:30,280 --> 01:33:34,920
Roman Bridger, director.
And brother.

1254
01:33:35,160 --> 01:33:37,600
She slammed the door in my face, Sid.
She said I was Rina's child...

1255
01:33:37,840 --> 01:33:39,840
and Rina was dead.

1256
01:33:40,080 --> 01:33:41,920
And it struck me.

1257
01:33:42,160 --> 01:33:45,200
What a good idea!
So I watched her.

1258
01:33:45,440 --> 01:33:49,160
I made a little home movie.
A little-little family film.

1259
01:33:49,400 --> 01:33:52,200
It seems Maureen--
Mom--

1260
01:33:52,440 --> 01:33:56,240
She really got around.
I mean, Cotton was one thing.

1261
01:33:56,480 --> 01:33:58,440
Everybody knew about that.

1262
01:33:58,680 --> 01:34:03,040
But Billy's father?
That was the key.

1263
01:34:03,280 --> 01:34:05,160
Your boyfriend didn't like seeing
his daddy in my film too much.

1264
01:34:05,400 --> 01:34:07,440
He didn't like it at all.

1265
01:34:07,680 --> 01:34:11,640
But once I supplied the motivation,
all the kid needed was a few pointers.

1266
01:34:11,880 --> 01:34:14,960
Have a partner to sell out in case
you get caught, find someone to frame.

1267
01:34:15,200 --> 01:34:17,400
It was like
he was making a movie.

1268
01:34:17,640 --> 01:34:21,960
You. This is all because ofyou.

1269
01:34:22,200 --> 01:34:25,480
I'm a director, Sid.

1270
01:34:25,720 --> 01:34:27,880
- I direct.
- Oh.

1271
01:34:28,120 --> 01:34:32,800
I had no idea that they were
gonna make a film of their own.

1272
01:34:33,640 --> 01:34:37,160
- Oh, shit.
- What a film it turned out to be, huh?

1273
01:34:37,400 --> 01:34:40,080
I mean, introducing Sidney,
the victim.

1274
01:34:40,320 --> 01:34:45,080
Sidney, the survivor.
Sidney, the star!

1275
01:34:58,800 --> 01:35:00,800
All right. You're gonna be all right.
Just apply pressure.

1276
01:35:01,040 --> 01:35:03,200
Here, take this.
Get the son ofa bitch.

1277
01:35:03,440 --> 01:35:04,880
Let's go.

1278
01:35:05,120 --> 01:35:07,840
Fine, you got what you wanted,
hero and villain face-to-face.

1279
01:35:08,080 --> 01:35:10,640
- Well, you know what happens now?
The villain dies!
- Exactly!

1280
01:35:10,880 --> 01:35:14,960
But I'm not the villain, Sid.
You are.

1281
01:35:15,200 --> 01:35:19,440
Here he is, the man who gave away
your mother's innocence.

1282
01:35:19,680 --> 01:35:21,920
Huh? What he did
to her made her a slut.

1283
01:35:22,160 --> 01:35:26,200
Didn't it? Huh? She never recovered from
that night, right here in this room.

1284
01:35:26,440 --> 01:35:29,760
They fucked her three ways from Sunday.
Ruined her life.

1285
01:35:30,000 --> 01:35:31,600
Ruined yours too,
didn't it, Sid?

1286
01:35:31,840 --> 01:35:34,120
You hate him, Sid?

1287
01:35:34,360 --> 01:35:39,720
Come on, I know you do.
I'm sure you do.

1288
01:35:39,920 --> 01:35:42,160
I know who you are.
I know what happened to my mother.

1289
01:35:42,400 --> 01:35:45,080
And I want you to understand,
I'm gonna make you pay!

1290
01:35:45,320 --> 01:35:47,080
That's what the police are gonna
find on Milton's answering machine...

1291
01:35:47,320 --> 01:35:50,720
right next to his lifeless,
mutilated corpse.

1292
01:35:50,960 --> 01:35:53,000
- What? Can't hear ya.
- You don't have to do this, Roman.

1293
01:35:53,240 --> 01:35:55,040
Just tell me what you want.
I can make it happen.

1294
01:35:55,280 --> 01:35:57,120
Any picture.
Name your budget. Script approval.

1295
01:35:57,360 --> 01:35:59,360
- Final cut!
- I already have it.

1296
01:35:59,600 --> 01:36:02,800
No!

1297
01:36:03,480 --> 01:36:05,240
God! You spineless bastard!

1298
01:36:05,480 --> 01:36:08,200
No, Sid, that would be you.
You did it all.

1299
01:36:08,440 --> 01:36:12,200
You did it, you called them all.
Even your closest friends.

1300
01:36:12,440 --> 01:36:14,720
Living in total isolation, the pressure
ofanother movie about you...

1301
01:36:14,960 --> 01:36:17,840
the discovery that Milton
destroyed Mommy dearest...

1302
01:36:18,080 --> 01:36:21,040
you finally just snapped!

1303
01:36:21,280 --> 01:36:25,480
One, two, three!

1304
01:36:26,480 --> 01:36:30,000
And who's our hero, huh?
The sole survivor. Who's the one...

1305
01:36:30,240 --> 01:36:33,880
who bravely faced down the psychopath
and killed her with her own knife?

1306
01:36:34,120 --> 01:36:36,240
You're gonna pay for the life
you stole from me, Sid.

1307
01:36:36,480 --> 01:36:40,040
For the mother, and for the family,
and for the stardom and--

1308
01:36:40,280 --> 01:36:42,320
Goddam it! Everything you have
that should've been mine!

1309
01:36:42,560 --> 01:36:45,440
God! Why don't you stop your whining
and get on with it?
I've heard this shit before!

1310
01:36:45,680 --> 01:36:47,800
- Stop!
- You know why you kill people,
Roman? Do you?

1311
01:36:48,040 --> 01:36:50,880
- I don't wanna hear it!
- Because you choose to!
There is no one else to blame!

1312
01:36:51,120 --> 01:36:54,200
- Stop it! Fucking damn it!
- Why don't you take
some fucking responsibility?

1313
01:36:54,440 --> 01:36:58,120
- Fuck you!
- Fuck you!

1314
01:37:09,360 --> 01:37:12,720
Sid? Sidney?

1315
01:37:19,920 --> 01:37:23,280
Sidney?

1316
01:37:30,040 --> 01:37:33,000
Sidney!

1317
01:37:45,160 --> 01:37:47,960
Sidney!

1318
01:37:50,040 --> 01:37:53,000
Leave her alone!

1319
01:38:02,440 --> 01:38:05,480
Dewey, do something!

1320
01:38:08,360 --> 01:38:12,720
- Stand back!
- Dewey!

1321
01:38:15,760 --> 01:38:19,440
Sid! Sid.

1322
01:38:41,800 --> 01:38:45,560
Sid?

1323
01:38:47,840 --> 01:38:51,440
Where is he?

1324
01:39:03,680 --> 01:39:06,800
Hey. Lose something?

1325
01:39:07,040 --> 01:39:10,240
Found something.

1326
01:39:30,800 --> 01:39:35,240
There's gotta be another way in there!
Come on!

1327
01:39:39,880 --> 01:39:44,400
You hurt her,
I swear I'll kill you!

1328
01:39:56,480 --> 01:40:00,560
-Dewey!
-Down this way. There's another hallway.

1329
01:40:10,880 --> 01:40:14,240
There's another door down here.

1330
01:40:19,800 --> 01:40:21,960
- This thing's not budging.
- Look around for something heavy.

1331
01:40:22,200 --> 01:40:26,200
- Go that way.
- Okay!

1332
01:40:49,760 --> 01:40:53,280
I shot you.

1333
01:40:56,840 --> 01:41:01,280
I guess we think alike.

1334
01:41:01,280 --> 01:41:03,920
Mother's dead.

1335
01:41:04,160 --> 01:41:07,520
And there is nothing
you can do about that.

1336
01:41:07,680 --> 01:41:10,760
I still got
to make my movie.

1337
01:41:11,000 --> 01:41:14,840
Stab 3, right?

1338
01:41:30,360 --> 01:41:34,120
Kincaid, hang in there.

1339
01:41:34,280 --> 01:41:39,200
Roman? It was Roman?

1340
01:42:01,600 --> 01:42:06,680
Be careful, Sid. Randy said
the killer's always superhuman.

1341
01:42:07,960 --> 01:42:11,600
Yeah, well,
he wasn't superhuman, Dewey.

1342
01:42:11,840 --> 01:42:15,440
He wasn't superhuman at all.

1343
01:42:19,360 --> 01:42:21,320
- You can't fuckin' kill me!
- Head!

1344
01:42:21,560 --> 01:42:23,720
- Head! Head, Dewey!
- What?

1345
01:42:23,960 --> 01:42:27,480
Head!
Shoot him in the head.

1346
01:42:38,480 --> 01:42:40,440
Thanks.

1347
01:42:40,680 --> 01:42:44,040
No problem.

1348
01:43:08,080 --> 01:43:10,360
Look.

1349
01:43:10,600 --> 01:43:12,640
Come on, Cherokee.
Come on.

1350
01:43:12,880 --> 01:43:17,400
- Yeah, she's doin' great.
- Yeah.

1351
01:43:20,920 --> 01:43:24,280
Look.

1352
01:43:24,560 --> 01:43:26,440
What are you doing with that?

1353
01:43:26,680 --> 01:43:30,240
Um, will you sign it
for me, Gale?

1354
01:43:30,480 --> 01:43:32,640
You hate that book.

1355
01:43:32,880 --> 01:43:35,880
Besides, I'm-l'm done
with that kind of reporting.

1356
01:43:36,120 --> 01:43:41,280
For me.
Will you sign it for me?

1357
01:43:42,440 --> 01:43:45,200
You're a nut.

1358
01:43:45,440 --> 01:43:48,400
Okay.

1359
01:43:56,760 --> 01:44:00,880
- Will you?
- Dewey.

1360
01:44:01,120 --> 01:44:04,480
I know it'll never work,
and you know it'll never work.

1361
01:44:04,720 --> 01:44:11,720
But what I'm asking is
just to see ifwe're wrong.

1362
01:44:12,040 --> 01:44:15,800
We don't know everything, Gale.

1363
01:44:16,640 --> 01:44:21,320
I mean, you thinkyou do, but--

1364
01:44:26,960 --> 01:44:30,400
You're a brave man,
Dewey Riley.

1365
01:44:30,800 --> 01:44:34,800
I'm really scared right now.

1366
01:45:15,880 --> 01:45:19,320
Inside.

1367
01:45:23,560 --> 01:45:26,600
Sid, we've been waiting for you.
We're gonna start a movie.

1368
01:45:26,840 --> 01:45:32,920
- What kind of movie?
- You have to come and see.

1369
01:46:00,000 --> 01:46:03,560
Take a little walk
to the edge of town

1370
01:46:03,800 --> 01:46:07,400
Now, spread your wings and fly

1371
01:46:07,640 --> 01:46:11,440
Don't the lights of the city
look so damn pretty

1372
01:46:11,680 --> 01:46:15,720
When you're flyin' so high

1373
01:46:15,960 --> 01:46:19,320
It's hard to know
about there down below

1374
01:46:19,560 --> 01:46:24,280
The streets fade
They're swimmin'deep in blood

1375
01:46:24,520 --> 01:46:31,120
It seems to make me
groan and cry

1376
01:46:31,720 --> 01:46:34,920
You really wanna know
what's wrong with this land

1377
01:46:35,160 --> 01:46:40,600
Just scratch your head
with your red right hand

1378
01:46:42,080 --> 01:46:46,400
I'm talkin'about blood, babe

1379
01:46:46,640 --> 01:46:50,440
It's in your veins

1380
01:46:50,680 --> 01:46:54,120
Your mommy and daddy

1381
01:46:54,360 --> 01:46:57,880
They've got the same

1382
01:46:59,360 --> 01:47:04,040
You're under the mirror
day after day

1383
01:47:04,280 --> 01:47:07,840
You see a pretty face
crumblin' away

1384
01:47:08,080 --> 01:47:14,840
As you become
your mom and daddy

1385
01:47:14,960 --> 01:47:19,280
Scream once, scream twice
Now scream again

1386
01:47:19,520 --> 01:47:25,280
Cover that face
with your red right hand

1387
01:47:36,760 --> 01:47:41,120
So, is this the end

